  "body": {
    "export_view": {
      "value": "<p>Release\u00a0Launched 9/29/16 4:11PM CT</p><p>This is a minor release with a few bug fixes.</p><h3 id=\"id-1.8.8-InventoryCount-ReconcileAllZeroVariance\">Inventory Count - Reconcile All Zero Variance</h3><p>The &quot;Reconcile All&quot; feature on the count screen\u00a0marks all counts with a zero variance as &quot;reconciled.&quot; <em><strong>No inventory records are adjusted when using the reconcile all\u00a0feature, and only the count record status is updated from &quot;counted&quot; to &quot;reconciled.&quot;</strong></em>\u00a0An issue was identified\u00a0with serialized item counts where it was not required to have all matching serials before a count could be marked as reconciled, therefore potentially missing some count records where the counted qty matched the instock qty, but the serial numbers did not all match instock serials. This has been updated, so that in the event that this occurs, the count record is skipped, and you are required to handle the reconciliation\u00a0of\u00a0the count directly. In this way, counts with mismatched serials will not be marked as reconciled without handling the serial number discrepancies.</p><h3 id=\"id-1.8.8-TicketItemDamaged/DefectiveDisplayLabel\">Ticket Item Damaged/Defective Display Label</h3><p>There were a few scenarios where the ticket item status would\u00a0show &quot;damaged&quot; when it should show &quot;defective.&quot; No accounting records are affected by this\u00a0update; only the status displayed on ticket screens is\u00a0affected by this update.</p>",
      "representation": "export_view",
